<TITLE> Khaleda pledges reinstatement of sacked officials </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 19 (bdnews24.com)  BNP chairperson Khaleda Zia on Wednesday pledged that her party would reinstate civil servants, police and army officials being stripped of their jobs when her party returns to power. Khaleda said, "Cases will be filed against all the corruption in future." The administration is now in a bad shape during now. "They have been stripping many government officials of their jobs illegally," Khaleda said. "I want to state that BNP will reinstate these officials if it comes to power the next time." Addressing prime minister Sheikh Hasina about her election manifesto Khaleda said, "She said, if her party goes to power, the prime minister, her relatives and cabinet members would present their wealth statements before the public." "But she did not keep her promise." Khaleda Zia alleged that the failure was because the government was looting public money. "And unable to calculate their wealth." 
